## Step 1 – Define Input Data

For negative mode:

```r
mat <- mat_raw_neg
meta <- meta_qc_neg
feature_info <- feature_neg_info
mode <- "neg"
```

For positive mode:

```r
mat <- mat_raw_pos
meta <- meta_qc_pos
feature_info <- feature_pos_info
mode <- "pos"
```

Standardize filenames and align metadata with the feature matrix.

```r
colnames(mat) <- tolower(colnames(mat))
meta$filename <- tolower(meta$filename)

mat <- mat[, meta$filename, drop = FALSE]

stopifnot(all(colnames(mat) == meta$filename))
```

Ensure all matrix values are numeric.

```r
mat <- mat %>%
  mutate(across(everything(), as.numeric)) %>%
  as.data.frame()
```

---

## Step 2 – Separate Sample Types

Identify biological samples, pooled quality controls (QCs), and analytical blanks.

```r
sample_ids <- meta %>%
  filter(sample_type == "sample") %>%
  pull(filename)

qc_ids <- meta %>%
  filter(sample_type == "qc") %>%
  pull(filename)

blank_ids <- meta %>%
  filter(sample_type == "blank") %>%
  pull(filename)
```

---

## Step 3 – Blank Filtering

### Purpose

Remove features originating from solvents, mobile phase, extraction artifacts, column bleed, laboratory contamination or instrumental background.

### Procedure

Calculate the mean intensity of each feature across biological samples and blanks.

```r
mean_sample <- rowMeans(mat[, sample_ids, drop = FALSE], na.rm = TRUE)
mean_blank  <- rowMeans(mat[, blank_ids, drop = FALSE], na.rm = TRUE)

mean_sample[is.nan(mean_sample)] <- 0
mean_blank[is.nan(mean_blank)] <- 0
```

Calculate the sample-to-blank ratio:

```r
blank_ratio <- mean_sample / (mean_blank + 1)
```

The `+1` prevents division by zero when the blank signal is absent.

Generate the filtering table:

```r
filter_blank_df <- tibble(
  feature_index = seq_len(nrow(mat)),
  feature_id = feature_info$id,
  mz = feature_info$mz,
  rt = feature_info$rt,
  mean_sample = mean_sample,
  mean_blank = mean_blank,
  blank_ratio = blank_ratio,
  keep_blank = blank_ratio > 5
)
```

### Criterion

Retain features when:

```text
Sample/Blank Ratio > 5
```

---

## Step 4 – QC Stability Filtering

### Purpose

Remove analytically unstable features.

### Procedure

Calculate mean intensity, standard deviation and relative standard deviation (RSD) across pooled QC samples.

```r
qc_mean <- rowMeans(mat[, qc_ids, drop = FALSE], na.rm = TRUE)

qc_sd <- apply(
  mat[, qc_ids, drop = FALSE],
  1,
  sd,
  na.rm = TRUE
)

qc_mean[is.nan(qc_mean)] <- 0
qc_sd[is.nan(qc_sd)] <- 0

qc_rsd <- 100 * qc_sd / qc_mean

qc_rsd[!is.finite(qc_rsd)] <- Inf
```

Generate the QC filtering table:

```r
filter_qc_df <- tibble(
  feature_index = seq_len(nrow(mat)),
  qc_mean = qc_mean,
  qc_sd = qc_sd,
  qc_rsd = qc_rsd,
  keep_qc = qc_rsd < 30
)
```

### Criterion

Retain features when:

```text
QC RSD < 30%
```

---

## Step 5 – Combine Filters

A feature is retained only when it passes both filtering criteria.

```text
Sample/Blank Ratio > 5
AND
QC RSD < 30%
```

```r
feature_filter_df <- filter_blank_df %>%
  left_join(filter_qc_df, by = "feature_index") %>%
  mutate(
    keep_final = keep_blank & keep_qc
  )
```

Generate the filtered matrix:

```r
mat_filt <- mat[
  feature_filter_df$keep_final,
  ,
  drop = FALSE
]

feature_filt <- feature_info[
  feature_filter_df$keep_final,
]
```

---

## Step 6 – Filter Summary

Summarize the number of retained features after each filtering step.

```r
filter_summary <- tibble(
  step = c(
    "Initial features",
    "After blank filter",
    "After QC RSD filter",
    "After combined filters"
  ),
  n_features = c(
    nrow(mat),
    sum(feature_filter_df$keep_blank),
    sum(feature_filter_df$keep_qc),
    sum(feature_filter_df$keep_final)
  )
)
```

